
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* A web server for java based web apps

* Free & Open Source

* Supports Java Technologies
	* Java Servlet
	* JSP - Java Server Page

* Also called servlet container

* Above Java 1.8+

* 8080

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Servlet

	- Is a specialized Java class in web app
	- Can handle server requests like GET, POST, PUT, DELETE
	- JSP is Request - Compile JSP by JDK -> Executed by Servlet Container - O/P HTML

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* End To End Life Cycle Management
* 4 Core Parts

	- Catalina
	- Jasper
	- Coyote
	- Cluster

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Catalina

	- Handles life cycle of servlet
	- init(), service(), destroy()

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Jsper

	- JSP Parser Engine
	- Converts JSP to Servlet

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Coyote

	- Is Network service
	- Transmits web requests to Container and End User
	- Also to integrate with another Web Server

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Cluster

	- As the name says
	- Used for load balancing

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

/tomcat/webapps - apps
/tomcat/bin - startup.sh
/tomcat/conf - configurations ex: service.xml for manager username and password

-------------------------------------------------------------------------